{"actual_usd":0.15852,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":183,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31155,"reply":"\"To the Father.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the bright square a second, buying half a beat because this one deserves a clean answer.* \"Not God pretending to talk into a mirror — the Son speaking to the Father. Same God, yes, but not the same Person.\"\n\n*I rest my forearms on my knees.* \"Gethsemane only gets strange if we flatten the Trinity. Jesus isn't a lone divine individual doing impressions. He's the Son, in real relation to the Father, and in his human life he prays exactly the way a real obedient man would: truly, painfully, without theater. 'Not my will, but yours' doesn't mean he isn't God. It means the Incarnation is real, and his human will is not fake.\"\n\n\"If you want, I can give you the short orthodox version or the more nuts-and-bolts version.\"","rolling_24h_usd":40.27016000000003,"run_id":"eb270ece-c01e-4726-9b28-b3130e1db2f4"}
